# Performance & Lightweight Code

## Imports

```python
# ❌ module-level — slows every launch
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# ✅ lazy — only when user opens Graphs tab
def build_graphs_tab(self, parent):
    from matplotlib.figure import Figure
    from matplotlib.backends.backend_tkagg import FigureCanvasTkAgg
```

## Data

- Load `data.json` once at init; hold in memory; write on save.
- Precompute summary stats on save, not on every dashboard refresh.
- Migrate to SQLite only when JSON load is measurably slow (>5MB or >500ms).

## UI

- Prefer `ttk` widgets. Avoid unnecessary `destroy()` + full rebuild; update in place on hot paths.
- Cache matplotlib `Figure` objects when underlying data unchanged.
- No background threads for simple JSON — sync I/O is fine at personal scale.

## Forbidden Without Explicit Approval

- pandas, numpy (beyond matplotlib's transitive use), Electron, Qt, web stacks, ORMs
- Network calls in core logging flow
- Saving chart PNGs to disk unless user exports

## Profiling First

Run `python -X importtime tracker.py` before any language rewrite or heavy refactor.
